# Legal Contract Information

## Extension Option
- A lease extension of up to 25 years is possible.
- The extension price is not included in the acquisition price and will depend on market prices and availability at the time.

## Lease Agreement
An Indonesian notarial lease deed (the “Lease Agreement”) will be signed by the Parties after the Unit Transfer.

## Payment Procedure
1. First payment: 50% (fifty percent) of the full price shall be paid latest 21 days after signing this agreement by THE SECOND PARTY.
2. Another 30% (thirty percent) from the remaining 50% shall be paid after the finish of structural elements (floors, walls, and ceiling).
3. The remaining 20% (twenty percent) is paid straight from the rental profit going forward.

## Leasehold Agreement
- The Developer guarantees to have the legal right to transfer the lease of the land to the Owner and carrying out this legal action is in accordance with and does not conflict with the law and the provisions referred to in the Original Land.
- The zoning of the Land allows the construction of a private residence;
- The leasehold period is valid until 01-06-2048 with a possible lease extension for up to 25 years.
- The minimum extension period is 10 years.

## Final Handover
Final handover of the documents of the villa shall be made based on the present Agreement and concurrently therewith the Developer shall hand over the following documents to the SECOND PARTY:
- Copy of Original of Land Master Lease Deed of land;
- Copy of Sub-lease Deed;
- Copy of land lease extension Deed;
- Copy of the building permit PBG and SLF which still in the progress of completion;
- Copy of last receipt of payment for PBB tax;
- Copy of other license related to the property if any; Copy of property floor plan etc.

## Communal Expenses
- Internet
- Maintenance cost of communal areas: (Façade maintenance, public pools, security, public parking, gardens)
- Drinking water
- Banjar fee TBA
- Other (toilet treats, cleaning products, pool chemicals, etc.)
- Rubbish collection
- Housekeeper cleaning and gardener
- Electrical power will be provided to the Unit but is not included in this Maintenance Fee and will be metered/paid for separately by the Owner.

## Return of Investment
1. Based on the "owners value" in this matter $25,000 USD (United States Dollars), the manager guarantees a minimum return of investment on an average of 12% (twelve percent) per annum for the property’s first three years of operation starting from the property's first day of operation: The 01 of April 2024.
2. Should the Unit fail to deliver a 12% Return of Investment on an average of the first three years of operation, the owner will be compensated for the loss of the manager. The compensation will fall no later than 30 days after the period.
3. The 12% return of investment is calculated and will be distributed after deduction of: Management fee and villa operation Cost of 30% (thirty percent).

## Personal Use of the Property
The owner has the option to use the property for personal use:
1. Bookings made by the owner need to be done directly with the manager and are subject to availability.
2. If the owner chooses to stay in the property, the operation and management fee doesn't cover the expenses of the period.
3. If the owner chooses to stay in the property, the days spent will be deducted 1-1 from the guaranteed return of investment.

## Profit Distribution / Payments
Profit distribution- The profit distribution to the owner is based on the “Value Point system”.
1. The revenue distribution to the owner shall be made by the manager to the owner quarterly (May, August, November, February) from the first day of operation.
2. All payments to the owner shall be calculated on the exchange rate of the manager's bank.
3. The owner will provide a bank account of own choice for earning distribution. Bank transfer fees and currency conversion fees (if any) are at the expense of the owner.

## Maintaining Property Standards
The manager shall maintain the buildings, appurtenances, and common areas of the property including without limitation all repairs, cleaning, painting, decorations, and alterations for example HVAC (heating, ventilation, and air conditioning systems), and MEP (mechanical, electrical & plumbing), carpentry, masonry, and such other routine repairs as are necessary or reasonably appropriate in the course of maintenance of the property (subject to the limitations of this Agreement).

## Reports
1. The manager shall prepare and provide a quarterly report with a clear overview of the rental income, the operation & management fee, and the net profit.
2. The manager shall prepare and provide an annual report with a clear overview of the rental income, the operation & management fee, and the annual return of investment.

## Notices
Any notice or other communication will be valid if sent to the postal address or email address last notified to the other Party and notice will be deemed to have been duly given or made as follows:
- if sent by personal delivery upon delivery at the address of the recipient;
- if sent by registered post two business days after the date of posting; and
- if sent by email upon dispatch to the email address of the recipient.

## General
- This Agreement and the documents referred to in it constitute the entire agreement and understanding between the Parties relating to the subject matter of this Agreement.
- Governing Law: This Agreement shall be governed by and construed and interpreted in accordance with the laws of Indonesia.
- Dispute Resolution: Any disputes shall be settled amicably by the Parties wherever practicable.

## Force Majeure
If any Party is prevented, hindered, or delayed in its performance of any of its obligations pursuant to this Agreement by reason of Force Majeure, that Party shall be excused from the performance of its obligations during the existence of the Force Majeure.

Notices to the manager should be sent to the “manager's Notice Address” and notices to the Owner should be sent to the “owner's Notice Address”. A Party must promptly notify the other Party of a change to its name, address, or email address for the purpose of this clause, and such change will be effective immediately upon receipt of the notification unless otherwise specified therein.

